<DocsLayout title="CI/CD SDK" activeSection="sdk">
  <h1>CI/CD SDK</h1>
  <p>The SEO Crawler SDK is a standalone CLI binary that runs SEO/GEO checks in your CI/CD pipeline. Catch SEO regressions before they reach production.</p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <h3>Build from source</h3>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/MarceloBD/free-seo-crawler.git
cd free-seo-crawler
make build-sdk
# Binary: bin/seo-crawler</code></pre>

  <h3>Download release binary</h3>
  <pre><code># Linux
curl -sL https://github.com/MarceloBD/free-seo-crawler/releases/latest/download/seo-crawler-linux-amd64 -o seo-crawler
chmod +x seo-crawler

# macOS
curl -sL https://github.com/MarceloBD/free-seo-crawler/releases/latest/download/seo-crawler-darwin-amd64 -o seo-crawler
chmod +x seo-crawler</code></pre>

  <h2>Scan Modes</h2>

  <h3>Full mode (live crawl)</h3>
  <p>Crawls a running server, following links and checking all pages.</p>
  <pre><code>seo-crawler --mode=full --url=http://localhost:3000</code></pre>

  <h3>Static mode (local HTML files)</h3>
  <p>Analyzes built HTML files directly — no server needed.</p>
  <pre><code>seo-crawler --mode=static --dir=./dist</code></pre>

  <h2>Auto-starting a Dev Server</h2>
  <p>The SDK can start your dev/preview server before crawling and stop it after:</p>
  <pre><code>seo-crawler \
  --mode=full \
  --start-cmd="npm run dev" \
  --wait-for=http://localhost:3000 \
  --url=http://localhost:3000</code></pre>

  <h2>Multiple Servers</h2>
  <p>When your app depends on both a frontend and a backend (or other services), pass multiple commands and URLs:</p>
  <pre><code># Via CLI flags (comma-separated)
seo-crawler \
  --mode=full \
  --start-cmd="go run ./cmd/server,npm run dev" \
  --wait-for="http://localhost:8080/api/health,http://localhost:3000" \
  --url=http://localhost:3000</code></pre>

  <p>Or as an array in the YAML config:</p>
  <pre><code>mode: full
url: http://localhost:3000
start_cmd:
  - "go run ./cmd/server"
  - "cd web && npm run dev"
wait_for:
  - http://localhost:8080/api/health
  - http://localhost:3000
wait_timeout: 90s
fail_on: high</code></pre>
  <p>All commands are started in parallel. The crawler waits for every URL in <code>wait_for</code> before starting. All processes are stopped when the scan finishes.</p>
  <p>Both fields accept a single string or an array in YAML. On the CLI, use comma-separated values.</p>

  <h2>Configuration File</h2>
  <p>Create a <code>.seo-crawler.yml</code> in your project root:</p>
  <pre><code>mode: full
url: http://localhost:3000
start_cmd: "npm run dev"
wait_for: http://localhost:3000
wait_timeout: 60s
fail_on: high
max_pages: 100
format: text
ignore:
  - uses_https
  - hsts_header</code></pre>

  <p>CLI flags override config file values.</p>

  <h2>CLI Flags</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Default</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>--mode</code></td><td><code>static</code> or <code>full</code></td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--dir</code></td><td>Directory with HTML files (static mode)</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--url</code></td><td>Server URL to crawl (full mode)</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--fail-on</code></td><td>Severity threshold for exit code 1</td><td><code>high</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--ignore</code></td><td>Comma-separated rule keys to skip</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--only</code></td><td>Comma-separated rule keys to run exclusively</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--start-cmd</code></td><td>Commands to start servers (comma-separated for multiple)</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--wait-for</code></td><td>URLs to poll until ready (comma-separated for multiple)</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--wait-timeout</code></td><td>Max wait time per URL (e.g. <code>30s</code>, <code>1m</code>)</td><td><code>30s</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--format</code></td><td><code>text</code> or <code>json</code></td><td><code>text</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--output</code></td><td>Write JSON report to file path</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--max-pages</code></td><td>Max pages to crawl</td><td><code>1000</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--config</code></td><td>Path to config file</td><td><code>.seo-crawler.yml</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Exit Codes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>0</code></td><td>All checks pass (no issues at or above threshold)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>1</code></td><td>Issues found at or above <code>--fail-on</code> severity</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>2</code></td><td>Configuration error</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>GitHub Actions Example</h2>
  <pre><code>name: SEO Audit
on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  seo-audit:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: "20"
          cache: "npm"

      - run: npm ci

      - name: Download SEO Crawler SDK
        run: |
          curl -sL https://github.com/MarceloBD/free-seo-crawler/releases/latest/download/seo-crawler-linux-amd64 -o seo-crawler
          chmod +x seo-crawler

      - name: Run SEO audit
        run: |
          ./seo-crawler \
            --mode=full \
            --start-cmd="npm run dev" \
            --wait-for=http://localhost:3000 \
            --url=http://localhost:3000 \
            --fail-on=high</code></pre>

  <h2>Ignoring Rules for Localhost</h2>
  <p>When testing localhost, some rules will always fail (e.g. HTTPS, HSTS). Ignore them in your config:</p>
  <pre><code>ignore:
  - uses_https
  - hsts_header
  - mixed_content</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
